      <blockquote class="calibre31">
        <blockquote class="calibre12">
          <span class="calibre18">TOM ROBBINS</span>
          <span class="calibre4"> has been called “a vital natural resource” by </span>
          <span class="calibre4">
            <span class="italic">The Portland Oregonian,</span>
          </span>
          <span class="calibre4"> “one of the wildest and most entertaining novelists in the world” by the </span>
          <span class="calibre4">
            <span class="italic">Financial Times</span>
          </span>
          <span class="calibre4"> of London, and “the most dangerous writer in the world today” by Fernanda Pivano of Italy’s </span>
          <span class="calibre4">
            <span class="italic">Corriere della Sera.</span>
          </span>
          <span class="calibre4"> A Southerner by birth, Robbins has lived in and around Seattle since 1962.</span>
        </blockquote>
